definition.value: This is an AE which is a collection of cerebrospinal fluid (CSF), without blood, located under the dural membrane of the brain.
This is an AE which is a common, sometimes chronic skin condition which presents as reddish bumps on the skin arranged in a circle or ring.
This is an AE which is a condition in the fetus characterized by an accumulation of fluid, or edema, in at least two fetal compartments.
This is an AE which is a condition in which the central nervous system of a person has multiple demyelinating lesions with atypical characteristics for those of standard multiple sclerosis (MS).
This is an AE which is a condition or lesion involving abnormal cells which are associated with an increased risk of developing into cancer.
This is an AE which is a cutaneous condition characterized by dependent edema from vasodilatory pooling.
This is an AE which is a cutaneous condition that develop in patients with an acute exacerbation of chronic edema, particularly of the lower extremities, and in the setting of anasarca.
This is an AE which is a cyst in the eyelid usually due to a blocked meibomian gland,typically in the middle of the eyelid, red, and not painful.
This is an AE which is a deposition of yellowish cholesterol-rich material that can appear anywhere in the body in various disease states.
This is an AE which is a fluid-filled bump associated with a joint or tendon sheath.
This is an AE which is a group of abnormal cells.

This is an AE which is a localized bleeding outside of subcutaneous blood vessels, due to either disease or trauma including injury or surgery and may involve blood continuing to seep from broken capillaries.
This is an AE which is a malignant and aggressive neoplasm with unclear molecular etiology.
This is an AE which is a malignant tumor in the mediastinum, the cavity that separates the lungs from the rest of the chest.
This is an AE which is a malignant tumor, a type of cancer that arises from transformed cells of mesenchymal (connective tissue) origin.
This is an AE which is a mass of cells (tumor) that lacks the ability to either invade neighboring tissue or metastasize (spread throughout the body).
This is an AE which is a pre-cancerous area of thick, scaly, or crusty skin.
This is an AE which is a primary cause of reduced vision following both cataract and successful vitreoretinal surgery.
This is an AE which is a rare clinical condition characterised by diffuse woody induration of skin commonly associated with diabetes mellitus,infections and monoclonal gammopathy.

This is an AE which is a rare condition. Desmoid tumors arise from cells called fibroblasts, which are found throughout the body and provide structural support, protection to the vital organs, and play a critical role in wound healing.
This is an AE which is a rare disorder defined as a pathological overgrowth of normal epidural fat.
This is an AE which is a rare skin disorder that primarily affects children under one year of age but can also be found in older children and adults.
This is an AE which is a rare tumor of the adrenal medulla composed of chromaffin cells, also known as pheochromocytes.
This is an AE which is a serious long-term complication in cancer survivors.
This is an AE which is a sharply demarcated yellowish deposit of cholesterol underneath the skin.
This is an AE which is a skin condition that most commonly presents with symmetrical round-to-oval red or violet plaques on the flanks, armpits, inner thighs, and lower abdomen.

This is an AE which is a syndrome (a set of signs and symptoms) that is the consequence of cancer in the body, specifically due to the production of chemical signaling molecules (such as hormones or cytokines) by tumor cells or by an immune response against the tumor.
This is an AE which is a term used synonymously with severe hypothyroidism.
This is an AE which is a tumor in the mediastinum, the cavity that separates the lungs from the rest of the chest.
This is an AE which is a tumor in the mediastinum, the cavity that separates the lungs from the rest of the chest. It contains the heart, esophagus, trachea, thymus, and aorta.
This is an AE which is a tumor made up of several different types of tissue, such as hair, muscle, teeth, or bone.
This is an AE which is a tumor that arises from the ependyma, a tissue of the central nervous system.
This is an AE which is a tumor that can develop on any skin or mucosal surface, but occurs on the tongue 40% of the time.
This is an AE which is a type of abnormal and excessive growth of tissue.
This is an AE which is a type of cancer that can form masses in the skin, in lymph nodes, in the mouth, or in other organs.
This is an AE which is a type of cancer that may be a bone sarcoma or a soft-tissue sarcoma.
This is an AE which is a type of connective tissue cancer in which the cells are spindle-shaped when examined under a microscope.

This is an AE which is a type of highly malignant cancer that most commonly arises within the lung, although it can occasionally arise in other body sites, such as the cervix, prostate, and gastrointestinal tract.
This is an AE which is a type of skin cancer that develops from the pigment-producing cells known as melanocytes in situ.
This is an AE which is a type of skin cancer that develops from the pigment-producing cells known as melanocytes.
This is an AE which is a type of skin infection which typically occurs as a cyst between the cheeks of the buttocks and often at the upper end.
This is an AE which is a usually benign (non-malignant) cyst in the pineal gland, a small endocrine gland in the brain.
This is an AE which is a vascular tumor that occurs on both mucosa and skin, and appears as an overgrowth of tissue due to irritation, physical trauma, or hormonal factors.
This is an AE which is an abnormal growth of tissue projecting from a mucous membrane.
This is an AE which is an ambiguous mass found in the neck area.
This is an AE which is an extremely rare long-term systemic disorder that involves the formation of granulomas and inflammation of blood vessels (vasculitis).
This is an AE which is an extremely rare long-term systemic disorder that involves the formation of granulomas and inflammation of blood vessels (vasculitis).

This is an AE which is an uncommon but distinctive acquired ichthyosiform dermatosis characterized by persistent dark, scaly, papules and plaques that tend to be localized predominantly on the central trunk.
This is an AE which is edema (accumulation of fluid causing swelling) in tissues perfused by the peripheral vascular system, usually in the lower limbs.
